<p>In February this year, Shakira reminded the world what a true superstar she is, as she joined Jennifer Lopez to perform at the halftime of the National Football League's Super Bowl LIV, at Hard Rock Stadium in Miami Gardens.</p>

<p>Shakira put on a showstopping and high-energy performance, racing through her hits including Whenever, Wherever, Waka Waka, and She Wolf. </p>

<p>Her trainer Anna Kaiser, whose danced-based cardio fitness AKT method combines toning and strength circuits, explained to Vogue how the star managed to pull off the intense routine on stage. </p>

<p>Lucky man: Shakira shares two children with her husband, footballer Gerard Piqué, who she has been married to since 2011</p>

<p>'Shakira is really focused on consistency with her workouts—the strength, the cardio, the stamina, the power, the flexibility, everything,' the trainer explained. </p>

<p>The pair had been starting their day ahead of the performance with a 90-minute dance interval workout, and it appears that Shakira - who has belly danced since she was a child - is still looking in better shape than ever.</p>

<p>'She will make some of the movements her own, adding flair with her hips,' Anna revealed. 'Even though it's super intense, she's still having fun!'</p>

